Using Stirling’s approximation,
\[
\frac{(n^2)!}{(2n)!}\approx \frac{\sqrt{2\pi n^2}\left(\frac{n^2}{e}\right)^{n^2}}{\sqrt{4\pi n}\left(\frac{2n}{e}\right)^{2n}}
= \frac{\sqrt{2\pi}\,n\; n^{2n^2}e^{-n^2}}{\sqrt{4\pi n}\;2^{2n}n^{2n}e^{-2n}}
= C\, n^{1/2}\, \frac{n^{2n^2-2n}}{2^{2n}}\, e^{-n^2+2n},
\]
for some constant \(C>0\). Since the dominant term is \(n^{2n^2}\), the ratio diverges to \(+\infty\). Thus,
\[
\lim_{n\to\infty}\frac{(n^2)!}{(2n)!}=+\infty.
\]

